The paper deals with the study of games for negotiations, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as negotiation is a common problem in multi-agent systems. The paper also discusses coalition problems, which are a fundamental concept in multi-agent systems and can be categorized under multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problems, which can be categorized under computational complexity (cs.CC) or logic in computer science (cs.LO).
